@barbellsncoffee_16_ I’m glad you asked, Jessica. Clear action items would include: 1) donations to BLM organizations, protestor bail-outs, and many other direct monetary forms of support 2) publicly support and amplify specific organizations and resources, petitions, seeing as the @philzcoffee Instagram account has 59,000 followers 3) *urge* investors and partner companies (Philz has a location inside of the Facebook campus, for example) to take further action on everything thus far. Firstly, I understand that Philz tries to be a company of political freedom for employees and customers, but as we do have a “zero tolerance for discrimination” policy it is important for any uneducated employee to attend the meeting tomorrow. Furthermore, which such a large platform I would like to see Philz provide more actual information as to how people can help. This would include links to places when people can sign petitions, donate, or simply further educate themselves https://blacklivesmatters.carrd.co/ is a great resource you could easily promote. I am also disappointed in philz for not support the movement in any way by donation. This could be even a small denomination of money to any credible organizations or local bail funds. I understand that it is possible Philz has lost profits over the last few months due to covid closures and continued pay but even so it would be extremely beneficial for Philz to donate. Not only would donation help directly fund the situation, but it would be incredible beneficial for Philz to lead by example. Pressure other companies to do better. Make it the norm for large corporations to stop ignoring the problem. Make it the norm for companies to display more than  performative activism. If Philz is serious about ridding any form of racism or discrimination in our customer and employee pool, these are necessary steps that must be taken

I want to preface this by saying that I was not asked to make a statement by Philz and am only choosing to respond because what I am seeing Philz being portrayed as is unfair.  I agree that the initial message was not specific enough on our stance against police brutality, racial injustice or racism in this country. I agree that to put out an initial statement showing more concern for our stores/roasting plants than concern for what we are actually protesting was wrong. But We as a black community can NOT continue to attack businesses for not responding “swiftly” enough or the exact way we want them to when they are literally telling us that they do not have the answers but are willing/open to listen. Yes, we should hold everyone accountable for making sure they are “putting their money where their mouth is” especially during such an important issue as this. And for those who have experienced racism in the work place, i will say there is no excuse for that and I do not stand behind that at all either.

For any employees currently working for Philz and are throwing backlash, you have seen that the majority of our home office staff as well as CEO, CPO, CFO are not black. So to assume that Philz will automatically/quickly be able to respond on this matter without having people of color in those positions who know exactly where/how to support is unfair. Philz has stated multiple times that they are open to any ideas and are more than willing to support the black lives matter movement in anyways we (the black community/employees) are able to help them come up with. We need time to have these conversations and educate wherever possible as opposed to just making a statement because it’s the right thing to do. This is not a time to attack, but to inform, educate and come up with REAL solutions that we both as a company and individual can act on to make this country a better place for the black community to live. I say all of this with the best intentions and hope to continue this conversation with my fellow black/white/Hispanic/Asian/etc peers of Philz as we push to live through our mission of bettering days, inclusion and equality. Update

We deeply appreciate and value the responses we’ve received and wanted to take a moment to acknowledge that we had the opportunity to reflect on our statement: 
We at Philz Coffee stand with those who are speaking out against racism and demanding justice for George Floyd. 
George Floyd’s senseless murder is yet another disturbing and painful reminder of systemic oppression and racial injustice. Philz Coffee is in full solidarity and support with our black communities. Because black lives matter. 
Equality, respect, peace, and love are core tenants to our culture. Our mission of bettering peoples days is also about bringing people together, creating community, and building relationships with people in our community. 
We have a responsibility to speak up, and to also listen. Right now we may not have all the answers; as such, we seek to be better by listening to those in our community who are grieving. To our community: we hear you, we see you, and we support you.

@jacobjaber
.
.

Original Message below:
The world feels a bit crazy at the moment. I wanted to provide an update surrounding the recent protests occurring in many cities across the country regarding the horrific murder of George Floyd. 
What happened is extremely disturbing. I stand for justice and peaceful protest that results in positive change. Philz stands for equality, respect, and love. We have a responsibility to create inclusive gathering places for our team and customers. With that said, putting people in danger is uncalled for. 
Some of the protests are near our stores and the roasting plant, and near the homes of team members. Our priority is the safety of our team members and customers. We want our customer community to know that we are actively monitoring the situation in partnership with our local leaders and working together to determine the best approach to protect the safety of our team and customers. 
We are here to serve you; however, please stay tuned to your local stores‘ social channel for updates as the situation unfolds. 
Please stay safe.

Meet Ryan, our Roasting Operations Manager, he's responsible for roasting the beans that go into each Cup of Love! He's sharing how he uses a clever dripper to brew iced coffee at home.
.
Here's a quick rundown for Iced Clever Dripper Pour Over:
- Rinse your filter
- Add 25 grams of medium ground coffee
- Pour 70 grams water, fully immersing grounds
- Let the coffee bloom for 45 seconds
- Add 180 grams of water and let brew for 2 minutes
- Place 4-5 ice cubes in the decanter
- After 2 minutes place the Clever on the decanter to drain
- Swirl decanter to melt ice
- Pour into a mug with fresh ice! If you're adding cream and sugar add the fresh ice after.
.
Enjoy!
